{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Male & Female employees should be treated the same when on shared parental leave",
        "additional_details": "At the moment there isn't any legal requirement, with some cases people making a claim that they are being treated less favourable than women on the same company and/or job, some being successful and some not.\r\nSome companies use the technicality that male employee on shared parental leave is treated no less favourably than a female employee on shared parental leave while they offer enhaced maternity pay a benefit only available to womans.",
        "background": "Because of the Equality Act 2010 woman and men should have the same company benefits as equal pay.\r\nAt the moment companies can offer a enhanced maternity pay that benefits only women can opt not to offer the same benefits to male employees wanting to take Shared Paternal Leave.",
